						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab near the temple of Kōḍi Honnavva.</hi></p>						

						<p>Indra III—A.D. 916-17.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Nityavarsha,</hi> is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 838, Dhātu,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 916-17.</hi> Further details of the date arenot given. It records the gift of <hi rend="italic">Vutāvura</hi> by Kachchavara Kāḍamma when <hi rend="italic">Mahāsamanta</hi> <hi rend="bold">Leṇṭeyarasa</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Purigeṛe Three-hundred.</hi> The gift was made in the presence of the <hi rend="bold">Hundred-and-twenty</hi> <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Paḷtiya-Maḷtavura.</hi> The record is published in (<hi rend="italic">Indian Antiquary,</hi> Vol. XII, p. 224).</p>						

						</summary>
